header.gameNote: HISPANIC COLLEGE FUND CLASSIC AT RALEIGH NC

article.headline: Delaware 67, Stetson 64
article.story: RALEIGH, N.C. (AP) -- Harding Nana had 24 points and 16 rebounds Saturday night to help Delaware rally from a 12-point second-half deficit and beat Stetson 67-64 in the Hispanic College Fund Classic. Calvin Cannon added 13 points for the Blue Hens (2-0), who face host North Carolina State on Sunday in the round-robin event. E.J. Gordon had 13 points for the Hatters (0-2), who lost to the Wolfpack on Friday night. The official attendance was listed at 9,741, but only a handful of fans -- scattered throughout the lower seating section of the RBC Center -- stayed for the game, which followed the Wolfpack's 91-59 win against The Citadel. The sleepy confines provided little energy for the Blue Hens, who instead turned to better man-to-man defense to claw their way back into the game. Stetson scored on four straight possessions midway through the second half, taking a 50-38 lead on 3-pointer and a spinning bank shot from Eric Diaz. The teams traded baskets until Delaware finally made its push, inching closer in the game's final four minutes before tying it at 60 on a long 3-pointer from Cannon with 2:57 left. That started an 8-0 run to put Delaware ahead to stay, beginning with a free throw from Herb Courtney for a 61-60 lead with 2:02 left. Zaire Taylor then made two plays to set up scores, finding Henry Olawoye for a bank shot inside and Nana for a dunk and a 65-60 lead with 32.5 seconds left. While Delaware pulled ahead, Stetson's offense struggled against the pressure defense. Karl Hollingsworth's jumper for a 57-50 lead with 6:21 left was Stetson's last field goal until a stickback from Gordon made it 67-64 with about 2 seconds left. The Hatters had a final chance when Taylor missed a pair of free throws with 1.8 seconds left. But Stetson had no timeouts, forcing Hollingsworth to heave the ball from beyond midcourt for a tying score. The ball bounced off the backboard to end the game.
